# tiwani-admin environment (template). Copy to .env.local and fill in. NEVER commit real values.
#
# SECURITY POSTURE (Decisions.md D16): this is the staff back office. It reads ACROSS tenants, which
# INVERTS the family product's RLS isolation, so it gets a SEPARATE origin + a SEPARATE auth audience +
# a SEPARATE process for the privileged data.
#
# RED LINES, enforced here by what is ABSENT:
#   - NO SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY. The RLS-bypass credential lives ONLY in the future tiwani-admin-api
#     process (D16), never in this frontend.
#   - NO family Supabase URL / anon key. This app does NOT talk to the family Supabase or the family api.
#   - Staff auth is a SEPARATE, STUBBED audience (see src/lib/staff-session.ts), never the family
#     Supabase Auth (no shared issuer, no token confusion).

# The admin API base URL the data-source toggle's LIVE mode reaches (tiwani-admin-api; only /health exists
# today). UNSET in dev: the app DEFAULTS to the clearly-labeled MOCK data layer (src/lib/mock/*), and
# flipping the toggle to LIVE with this unset throws a clear "Live API not configured" error. Set it to
# point LIVE mode at a running admin-api; the data endpoints are not built yet, so a live read of one
# surfaces a clean empty state + a "this endpoint is not available yet" toast. The seam lives in
# src/lib/admin-api/client.ts (the reusable mock/live wrapper) and the mode in src/lib/admin-api/mode.ts.
NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_API_URL=
